				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Fumbling keys and sorry at melee<a name="52802"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 20 04 11:29 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Did my first Ldon last night.  WoW! In 25 min I made 16pp and 44% experience at lvl 22.  However, I wasn't the best representative of barding.  We had two bards, so I did an awkward, for my set up, twist of Haste1, bellow5, Mana8, weaving in heal7, or mezz4, when necessary.  I had the biggest problem fumbling with keys trying to target the adds for mezz.  Is there a better way?
<br />

<br />
I used my cursor to target but had trouble targetting.  I changed my camera view but it did not always give me a better targetting angle.  I would fumble around for about 6 seconds before my mezz would land and then sometimes the members had engaged the mob because it was on our healer or mage.  I had to mezz it again to get it to stick and for the group member to back off.  (I'm thinking about making a macro for &quot;I'm mezzing %t!)
<br />

<br />
I also am still meleeing for 1-8 dmg with my 4/23 hammer and my 4/19 dagger.  Both add 3 dex and some agi and mana but I'm wondering if I need better weapons or to get my pierce and blunt skills up.  Those skills are in the mid 40s.  
<br />

<br />
I really like my bard. I get groups easy but cannot solo a blue without mez/heal.  I would like to melee better.
<br />

<br />
Urbanknight the Poetwarrior</span></td>
