				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Fumbling keys and sorry at melee<a name="52810"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 20 04 11:51 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Gratz on your new bard. As far as twisting goes there is a good post on it in the guides section but after 63 levels I have found the best method is to first determine the needs of the group and just go with that. I put all my song gems in the hotkey box lined up in the order that is needed. Example:
<br />

<br />
1- lull
<br />
2- MR buff
<br />
3- MR debuff for Mob
<br />
4- Mana song
<br />
5- haste
<br />
6- overhaste
<br />
7- slow
<br />
8- mez
<br />

<br />
I generally twist 4 songs so based on the type of mob, caster or meelee I will move my hand. I twist 2-5 for the casters or 4-7 for the meelees. The purpose is to create a general cadence for the twists this way and make the process easier to manage.
<br />

<br />
Also, be sure to check the options (Alt-O) keyboard/targetting setting getting use to toggling between targets will help you mezzing in the long run.
<br />

<br />
By the way, toe to toe meelee is hard to do less your ubah twinked. You will get better at it though.
<br />

<br />
Hope this helps,
<br />

<br />
Hadyen Singsaditty
<br />
63 bard - Terris Thule</span></td>
