				<td colspan="2"><span>for your level those weapons arent by any means horrible.  if you have the extra cash and want to spend it, there is better, but those arent too bad for 22.
<br />

<br />
the only way you're gonna get those melee skills up is to use them.  i'm curious as to how you leveled to 22 and still have melee skills in the mid 40s?  had you been using 1hs most of that time?  either way, you're only gonna get better with practice and that's a great level to start.  ldons are pretty good for getting those skills up, grouping works well too.  just get somewhere that you can beat on dark blue or stronger mobs, get some dex buffs (agi if you're gettin hit so you can raise defense/dodge faster), and sing your best haste.
<br />

<br />
for key setups, it's all up to you.  there is no specific way that works awesomely for everyone.  just figure out a key set up that you can learn and then just get used to it and eventually you'll memorize it.  i personally just have my spell gems in hotkeys 1-8, then swap out the last 2 depending on what i'm doing - assist, tracking, couple set up for calling out my camp in certain zones, a pulling macro, etc.  i then have the hotkeys set up on the number pad 1-9 (10th one i ususally have the button for callin out my camp in /ooc and i dont have that on a key so i dont accidently push it).  again, it's all up to you though.  once you get a setup worked out just use it and you'll get into it and be able to switch songs easily.</span></td>
