				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Fumbling keys and sorry at melee<a name="53220"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 22 04 10:46 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I recommend that you establish a pattern in the way that you memorize your songs and make your songlists.  There are a couple of reasons for this.
<br />

<br />
If you change from one songlist to another (using the right-click the spellbook thingie) you will only forget and rememorize the songs that are different.  In otherwords, if you ALWAYS have selos in slot 8, then when you change song lineups, you do NOT lose selos and rememorize it.  That's what would happen if, say, one songlist had it in slot 7, and the next one in slot 8.
<br />

<br />
Why does this matter?  I will give you a little scenario.  I was grouped in Plane of Nightmare once in my early 50s.  We tried to do the Hobgoblins, and the group wiped, except for me and the Necro who Feigned Death.  So, I run away, then mem my Chant Kite solo lineup.  Well, before I could get them all memmed, I had to stand up and run away again.  The GOOD thing was that Selos was still there the whole time, because I had it in the same slot on both songlists.
<br />

<br />
If you establish a pattern for how you mem your songs, then which hotkey finger it is on will always be the same.  Here is my system:
<br />

<br />
1- battle song
<br />
2- battle song
<br />
3- battle song
<br />
4- Mez (or fourth chant for chantkite)
<br />
5- Lull (or snare for chant kite setup)
<br />
6- Charm (or my pulling song, usually a debuff at lvls where charm doesn't work anymore)
<br />
7- Regen (Heal or Mana or Both when you get those songs)
<br />
8- Selos (or Invis in indoors, or Cancel Magic for breaking charm when groupd indoors / LDoN)
<br />

<br />
Usually, my songlist has Selos in it, and I change it after zoning into an LDoN mission.
<br />

<br />
Now, you can ALSO have different Hotkey Banks set up.  There are two little arrows on your hotkey bank on either side of the &quot;page&quot; number.  Shift - Number will change which hotkey page you are looking at.  Your hotkey are &quot;saved&quot; automatically as part of your UI settings.  As long as you are playing on the same character, on the same machine, your hotkey banks will be the way you left them.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
